==English==

===Transitive verb===
{{en-verb|sprinkl|ing}}

#To cause (a substance) to fall in fine [[drop]]s (for a liquid substance) or small pieces (for a solid substance).
#:''The confectioner sprinkled icing sugar over the cakes.''
#To [[cover]] (an object) by sprinkling a substance on to it.
#:''The confectioner sprinkled the cakes with icing sugar.''

====Translations====
*Finnish: [[sirotella]] (1,2), [[pirskottaa]] (1,2)
*Spanish: [[rociar]], [[salpicar]]

===Noun===
'''sprinkle''' (''plural:'' '''sprinkles''')

#A light covering with a sprinkled substance.
#:''He decorated the Christmas card with a sprinkle of glitter.''
#A light rain shower.

====Synonyms====
*(''light covering with a sprinkled substance''): [[sprinkling]]

